570–Afdød","–Male":"Afdød","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England"},"nl":{"–":"Overleden","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Overleden","–Male":"Overleden","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England"},"en":{"–":"Deceased","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Taylor","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: occupational name for a tailor, from Anglo-Norman French, Middle English <i>taillour</i> ‘tailor’ (Old French <i>tailleor</i>, <i>tailleur</i>; Late Latin <i>taliator</i>, from <i>taliare</i> ‘to cut’). The surname is extremely common in Britain and Ireland. In North America, it has absorbed equivalents from other languages, many of which are also common among Ashkenazic Jews, for example German   Schneider   and Hungarian   Szabo  . It is also very common among African Americans.","In some cases also an Americanized form of French   Terrien   ‘owner of a farmland’ or of its altered forms, such as   Therrien   and   Terrian  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Tayloe","meanings":["Altered form of English, Scottish, and Irish   Taylor  ."]},{"name":"Schneider","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Otto, Franz, Erwin, Fritz, Dieter, Manfred, Heinz, Alois, Ewald, Helmut.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): occupational name for a tailor, literally ‘cutter’, from Middle High German <i>snīder</i>, German <i>Schneider</i>, Yiddish <i>shnayder</i>. The same term was sometimes used to denote a woodcutter. This surname is also established in many other parts of Europe, notably in France (Alsace and Lorraine), the Netherlands, Hungary, Poland, and Czechia. In Czechia, Slovakia, Croatia, and Slovenia it is also established in Slavicized forms (see 2 below). In part, <i>Schneider</i> is a Gottscheerish (i.e. Gottschee German) surname, originating from the Kočevsko region in Lower Carniola, Slovenia (see   Kocevar  ). Compare   Sneider   1,   Snider   1, and   Snyder   1.","Germanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Šnajdr</b> or <b>Šnajder</b>, and Czech <b>Šneidr</b>, <b>Šneider</b>, <b>Šnejdr</b>, and <b>Šnejder</b>, surnames of German origin (see above)."]},{"name":"Tayler","meanings":["English: variant of   Taylor  ."]},{"name":"Tailor","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Pravin, Dilip, Mahesh, Sanjay, Kanchan, Kaushik, Manilal, Mohanlal, Navnit, Shailesh, Ajay, Alpana.","Indian (Gujarat and Mumbai): mainly Parsi occupational name from the English word <i>tailor</i>.","English: variant of   Taylor  ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":33,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":42,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":53,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Taylor was born in Hemsby, Norfolk, England. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Taylor est né à Hemsby, Norfolk, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England","lifeSummary":"Taylor wurde in Hemsby, Norfolk, England geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn und 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Desede","–Male":"Desede","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1597":"1597","1570":"1570","1549":"1549","Hemsby, Norfolk, England":"Hemsby, Norfolk, England"},"id":{"–":"Telah Meninggal","1535–1597":"1535–1597","1570–Female":"1570–Telah Meninggal","–Male":"Telah Meninggal","1569":"1569","